From: Paulo Alcantara <pc@manguebit.com>
Date: Tue, 2 Apr 2024 16:33:53 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] smb: client: fix potential UAF in
 cifs_debug_files_proc_show()
Git-commit: ca545b7f0823f19db0f1148d59bc5e1a56634502
References: bsc#1225172, bsc#1223532, CVE-2024-26928
Patch-mainline: v6.9-rc3

Skip sessions that are being teared down (status == SES_EXITING) to
avoid UAF.

Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Paulo Alcantara (Red Hat) <pc@manguebit.com>
Signed-off-by: Steve French <stfrench@microsoft.com>
Acked-by: Enzo Matsumiya <ematsumiya@suse.de>
---
 fs/smb/client/cifs_debug.c |    2 ++
 fs/smb/client/cifsglob.h   |   10 ++++++++++
 2 files changed, 12 insertions(+)

--- a/fs/smb/client/cifs_debug.c
+++ b/fs/smb/client/cifs_debug.c
@@ -248,6 +248,8 @@ static int cifs_debug_files_proc_show(st
 	spin_lock(&cifs_tcp_ses_lock);
 	list_for_each_entry(server, &cifs_tcp_ses_list, tcp_ses_list) {
 		list_for_each_entry(ses, &server->smb_ses_list, smb_ses_list) {
+			if (cifs_ses_exiting(ses))
+				continue;
 			list_for_each_entry(tcon, &ses->tcon_list, tcon_list) {
 				spin_lock(&tcon->open_file_lock);
 				list_for_each_entry(cfile, &tcon->openFileList, tlist) {
--- a/fs/smb/client/cifsglob.h
+++ b/fs/smb/client/cifsglob.h
@@ -2226,4 +2226,14 @@ struct smb2_compound_vars {
 	struct smb2_file_link_info link_info;
 };
 
+static inline bool cifs_ses_exiting(struct cifs_ses *ses)
+{
+	bool ret;
+
+	spin_lock(&ses->ses_lock);
+	ret = ses->ses_status == SES_EXITING;
+	spin_unlock(&ses->ses_lock);
+	return ret;
+}
+
 #endif	/* _CIFS_GLOB_H */
